properties.name: Turitea
properties.description: Altitude 150 metres. PNH, at the base of the upper dam, not the lower. (code PNH from "Palmerston North Mini Hydro") Declared connected to Bunnythorpe, much further away (indeed, beyond) Linton.

properties.name: Turitea
properties.description: Altitude 150 metres. TRT, appears to be another code for the Turitea 200KW scheme (commissioned 2002), though it might refer to the Turitea substation north of Linton. It is declared connected to Linton anyway.

properties.name: Two Mile Road
properties.description: Altitude 30 metres. TMR, junction, possibly where the line crosses Two Mile Line Road.

properties.name: Upcot Saddle

properties.name: Upper Hutt

properties.name: Upper Rakaia
properties.description: Altitude 440 metres. URK, and an administrative tangle. The supply line leaves the Coleridge substation heading NW to cross the upper Rakaia via Woolshed Hill, Mt Algidus station, (heading SW towards Glenrock stream) river to supply a few farms (on the "Ashburton" side), then recrosses to supply a few more near Manuka Point.

properties.name: Waharoa
properties.description: Altitude 50 metres. Dairy factory nearby, maybe with its own generation.

properties.name: Waiheke
properties.description: Altitude 10 metres. Marked as "Transformer station" on the topographic map, so possibly not an actual substation. The island obtains power via a cable from Auckland, but possibly not involving this location.

properties.name: Waihi Transformer House
properties.description: Altitude 90 metres. Somewhere nearby. Terminus of the early transmission line from Hora Hora in 1914. The 1904 Cornish Pumphouse (coal-fired) was kept ready until 1929 against power failures.

properties.name: Waihopai Spy Station

properties.name: Waimahia

properties.name: Waiotaka
properties.description: Altitude 375 metres. in a shipping container, it appears.

properties.name: Waipori
properties.description: Altitude 170 metres. WPG, code used when WPI is forgotten.

properties.name: Waipori
properties.description: Altitude 170 metres. WPV, village, presumably Waipori Falls.

properties.name: Wairoa Dam
properties.description: Altitude 270 metres. WWD, part of the water supply for Auckland thus "Watercare Wairoa Dam" or "Wairoa Watercare Dam". Not "Westwind", the Makara Wind Farm.

properties.name: Waitakere
properties.description: Altitude 160 metres. WWR, part of the water supply system. Possibly here.

properties.name: Western Road

properties.name: Western Road
properties.description: Altitude 18.6 metres. WET, possibly here, or rather, on both sides.

properties.name: Weston
properties.description: Altitude 100 metres. Since October 2007. The part-complete but paused (2011) Weston cement plant SE will have its own substation.

properties.name: Westport
properties.description: Altitude 7.9 metres. WPT, near a cement works, Cape Foulwind, well west of Westport and possibly not supplying it.

properties.name: Wether Burn

properties.name: Whangatane

properties.name: Whareroa

properties.name: Wharewaka

properties.name: Wheao
